biography_text: STEIL, Bryan, a Representative from Wisconsin; born in Janesville, Rock County, Wis., March 30, 1981; graduated from Joseph A. Craig High School, Janesville, Wis., 1999; B.S. Georgetown University, Washington, D.C., 2003; J.D., University of Wisconsin, Madison, Wis., 2007; staff, United States Representative Paul D. Ryan of Wisconsin, 2003-2004; lawyer; elected as a Republican to the One Hundred Sixteenth Congress (January 3, 2019-present).
